y supports 6 sections or if the consolidation to 5 is justified by the actual content organization.\n\nLooking at my findings now, there's a minor omission about two of the four patterns (戻り値確認パターン) being undocumented with a note that explanations will be added in the next publication. Since the knowledge file should reflect what's currently documented, flagging this absence helps prevent the AI from attempting to answer questions about patterns that genuinely aren't covered yet—even though it's provisional text tied to a future release.\n\nI'm also identifying two other minor omissions: the practical reason why the ID_GENERATE table needs initialization before tests (to ensure predictable numbering for result verification), and the implementation detail about appending 'Err' to IDs to mix normal and error test cases within the same Excel sheet. Both are useful operational guidance that got lost in the consolidation.\n\nNow I'm double-checking the severity assessment—none of these gaps actually undermine the core patterns being described, so they're all legitimately minor. Let me verify there aren't any fabrications by cross-referencing against the source material, particularly around how s4 uses group IDs with the `assertTableEquals` method. Looking at the source more carefully, I see that ID_GENERATE tables need to be pre-initialized before insert tests run, otherwise the auto-number generation results become unpredictable and verification fails. This is a critical constraint that the knowledge file completely misses in s3. So I'm confirming three minor omissions: the undocumented DB search patterns in s1, the ID_GENERATE initialization requirement in s3, and the error test data naming convention in s5.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":24190,"cache_read_input_tokens":29873,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":24190,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":8},"context_ma